What rules should parents have for their teenagers? Can children help out on the road, visit them, talk to them and attend school? What can a young person do for an adults and adolescent with anxiety, ADHD, panic attacks, trouble sleeping and hallucinations? Are teenagers competent enough to act as leaders or entertain adults and can a parent also hold on to them in time? The panel includes physicians, social workers, scientists and psychiatrists from both professions. As Dr. and Professor Wirt looks to her next big initiative to put together an active peer-